<paragraph blockId="44.[189,1399,622,798]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<bibRefCitation author="Richards O. W." box="[189,382,622,649]" firstAuthor="Richards" journalOrPublisher="Annals and Magazine of Natural History" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="531 - 535" part="9" refId="ref25830" refString="Richards O. W. 1967. On a collection of Sphaeroceridae (Diptera) from the Galapagos Islands. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (Series 13) 9: 531 - 535." title="On a collection of Sphaeroceridae (Diptera) from the Galapagos Islands" type="journal article" year="1967">Richards (1967)</bibRefCitation>
originally described this species as a 
<emphasis box="[845,1000,622,648]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Trachyopella</emphasis>
Duda, 1918 (then a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Olivier, 1813" authorityName="Olivier" authorityYear="1813" box="[189,473,660,686]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Leptocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,308,661,686]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Leptocera</emphasis>
Olivier, 1813
</taxonomicName>
), a placement that was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rohacek J. &amp; Marshall S. A." box="[892,1221,660,687]" firstAuthor="Rohacek" journalOrPublisher="Monografie III. Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Torino" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" refId="ref26146" refString="Rohacek J. &amp; Marshall S. A. 1986. The genus Trachyopella Duda (Diptera, Sphaeroceridae) of the Holarctic Region. Monografie III. Museo Regionale di Scienze Naturali, Torino." title="The genus Trachyopella Duda (Diptera, Sphaeroceridae) of the Holarctic Region" type="book" year="1986">Roháček &amp; Marshall (1986)</bibRefCitation>
in their review of Holarctic 
<emphasis box="[333,488,697,723]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Trachyopella</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pitkin B. R." box="[501,654,697,723]" firstAuthor="Pitkin" journalOrPublisher="W. Richards. Occasional Papers on Systematic Entomology, London" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" pagination="1 - 44" part="6" refId="ref25794" refString="Pitkin B. R. 1989. A review of the Sphaeroceridae (Diptera) described by O. W. Richards. Occasional Papers on Systematic Entomology, London 6: 1 - 44." title="A review of the Sphaeroceridae (Diptera) described by O" type="journal article" year="1989">Pitkin (1989)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Richards" authorityYear="1967" box="[792,895,698,723]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Leptocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opuntiae">
<emphasis box="[792,895,698,723]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">opuntiae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rohacek" authorityYear="1987" box="[929,1043,697,723]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Rudolfina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[929,1043,697,723]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Rudolfina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in view of its modified female cerci. Examination of 
<typeStatus box="[452,503,735,761]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">type</typeStatus>
specimens, including male and female terminalia, supports the treatment of this species as a 
<emphasis box="[383,538,772,798]" italics="true" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">Trachyopella</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
